ign=top bgcolor=#11221a class=headings><font color=#FFFFFF>Comment</font></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ufenye.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Fenye</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>The Queen of Discord</span><br>  Posts: 1844<br> <font color=#CC9900>(5/22/01 4:08:24 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://people.mn.mediaone.net/timelord81/images/fenye.jpg hieght=285 width=129></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Paladins... useless?</span><hr size=1> For a long time, paladins were extraordinarily powerful. We had healing power equivalent to druids and shamans, although usually not as much mana, we had buffs that were only one buff line less powerful than clerics, and we could dish out alot of damage, while still taking quite a bit. <br>
<br>
Paladins reigned supreme in places like Kithicor woods, Plane of Hate, and Lower Guk, where our Ghoulbanes dished out 162 damage each proc, and a 15dam 34delay sword was a very good sword to wield. Paladins were welcomed into groups with open arms, as they were very good at controlling aggro with thier stuns (and sometimes, undead nukes) and rooting, and thier ability to Lay Hands was a great boon to the group. A tank with two lives or the ability to save another with a touch of a button was a great asset indeed.<br>
<br>
Then we hit level 51, and 52, and 53, and so on. With each progressing level, our power was quickly fading, and we became unwanted in groups. Rangers had roughly the same AC as us, but dealt out massive amounts of damage, overshadowing a paladin completely. ShadowKnights were the kings of taunting, with thier line of necromantic spells. Warriors were vastly stronger than paladins, in nearly every area of a tank. What could we do then? We couldn't back up heal anymore, as Greater Healing and Superior healing was nothing but a bandaid to warriors. Our buffs were completely useless, as every group basically demands a cleric. We have two group friendly spell buffs.. Divine Glory and Divine Strength, but those only gave an extra 100-200 hp, and the Ranger line of group buffs (STR of Nature) was far more in demand, with giving 75hp and 25atk. <br>
The only thing we were good for, was our Lay of Hands, and that actually became a failure to groups. Once we used our LH, we couldn't do it again for another 72minutes. And often times, when the situation called for the Laying of Hands, the group was in so much trouble that everyone was going to die no matter what.<br>
<br>
On raids, we don't hold a candle to anyone else. Enchanters mana sieve and mez extras, as well as hasting the party. Druids could nuke and dot. Rangers, rogues, monks and warriors did damage. Wizards and mages nuked. Necromancers dot'd and summoned corpses. ShadowKnights pulled the area clean and once raid started, did thier damage too. Paladins? Know what I did my last raid? I was the sacrifice. The raid sent me out to die, because that was all I was useful for. I ran out, and placed Divine Aura upon myself, and let Trakanon follow me to the back of his lair before killing me in a matter of seconds. That's all paladins are good for now. Dying so the others can live.<br>
<br>
I have no pride in my class anymore. I used to be such an avid supporter of Paladins.. but I am just too depressed about them now. I sit at sebilis for hours, and sometimes wouldn't find a group in DAYS. I am not lying. I have been leveling so slowly, my friends pass me up. They are out there winning all sorts of really nice equipment, gaining levels 10 times as fast as I am, all the while I'm sitting at the zone LFG.<br>
<br>
What is there to be happy about in being a paladin? I have a nice sword, yes, but it's not that great now that I look at it. It's so slow, when I miss a swing, I lose out on alot of possible damage. I end up doing so little damage in fights, that I can barely taunt things anymore, especially if a ranger is in my group. My offensive spells are pathetic. I can stun a mob, and keep him stunned for a little while, but then my mana runs out after a few fights. My only dd does a pitiful 125 damage. All of my other equipment downright sucks at my level. I'm level 58, and have been playing for two years. I took my time to go to raids, and win my Valorium, and for awhile I was &quot;well equipped&quot;. But now, I pretty much need BETTER than that to be on par with the others at my level. Up until a few days ago, I still wore Adamantite Epaulets. Now I have an obulus death shroud. It's ok, but nothing like I wanted. I could raid the Hole for Granite Spaulders, but I'd never get that.<br>
<br>
I have tried to go on raids, but I just don't get invited. Nobody wants a paladin around, and although there will probably be some sympathy posts on this thread, everyone knows it's true. Paladins are useless.<br>
<br>
I'm level 58. A worthless, level 58 paladin. How I got this far amazes even me, and although I have alts, I don't care to take the time out to level them up high enough to replace Fenye.<br>
<br>
Honestly, I don't think I can find one thing useful about the paladin class other than being the &quot;lamb&quot; of the raids. <br>
<br>
sigh. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uaquasoultroll.showPublicProfile?language=EN>AquaSoulTroll</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Aqualungg_my_friend</span><br>  Posts: 306<br> <font color=#CC9900>(5/22/01 4:46:43 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Paladins... useless?</span><hr size=1> ive heard flash of light is a big taunt spell.  and costs barely any mana.  It wont make mobs run if your in melee range.  dunno if it works but might be worth a try.<br>
