Anyway, back to the paladins, the paladins' ability to stun might seem small to you, but imagine a ranger or rogue who has majorly aggroed the critter and getting pounded, his jolt was resisted or getting interrupted or evade not working, who else can get that critter off their backs? The paladin can either root or use his stuns to buy them time to either back away from the critter or for the healer to get a heal in. Sure SKs can also land a major taunt spell and get the critter to turn on himself, but my point is that paladins can do that too, and they have the AC and HPs to tank. Warriors on the other hand can only keep hitting that taunt key and hope that by some miracle he will shoot to the top of the hate list.<br>
