58th kata <BR></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ukyrnik.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kyrnik</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://kyrnik.homestead.com/files/Bullet_29542.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 59<br> <font color=#CC9900>(5/22/01 5:27:59 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://kyrnik.homestead.com/files/resizeupdate.jpg  align=left height=170 width=127></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Paladins... useless?</span><hr size=1> Fenye,<br>
I can agree and relate to many parts of your post.  I've been playing my current character for a full year now.  I have a 52nd level human pally (retired), and my current is a 52nd level High elf pally.  I have always been fond of the paladin class.  I didn't like always being blind as a bat, and having low mana, so I created the high elf instead and focused more on cleric type skills.  <br>
<br>
One thing that I pride myself in is being a class that can do a little of everything.  We can't heal and buff like clerics, and we can't tank like warriors.  But we are probably the most well rounded class when it comes to those skills that respectively define those classes.  No other class can really stack up to our versatility.  Certainly, Lay on Hands is one of our defining traits, but we all know it's use is limited.  I believe our role is clearly a utility character.<br>
<br>
Frankly we don't go into every fight looking to tank like a warrior.  Rather a paladin has to adapt to the group which he/she is in and determine which style best suits that particular instance.  If your heavy on tanks, then a paladin may very well assist the cleric on healing and buffs.  If your group is caster heavy, then the paladin switches to tank mode and takes the brunt of the damage.  No other class can be as flexible, IMO.<br>
<br>
I could go on and on, but it's not going to be anything that hasn't been said before.  The paladin class is not useless as everyone seems to think.  IMHO, I think we will see a few more big changes to the class balancing within the next few months.  Perhaps this will change the way Paladins are perceived across the servers.  I guess we will just have to wait and see.  <br>
<br>
Good luck to you on your way to becoming a Crusader.<br>
